<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="23Nov1925"><font color="red">23 November 1925</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I am not going into the clinic this morning &hellip; scopolamine &hellip; The &lsquo;scopo&rsquo; obstructs my sight in reading and I cannot finish <b><font face="wake">D</font></b>d before Wednesday. (25 November 1925) I must do this before I go in if I am to have any peace &hellip; I need another &pound;80 &hellip; to prevent myself from being troubled in Bulldogham Palace &hellip; It is  a dreadful bore especially now that my slow brain has got to work well after two months&apos; labour &hellip; Your MS this time will be partly written by Lucia (who calls it &lsquo;cinese&rsquo; (Chinese). I mean the penscript not the pencil draft. It will be finished tomorrow surely &mdash; of course only as a first draft but I perceive that I have written more of the book than I had thought. </div>
